# Canonical "audit user-run commands" rule (f3 §3.5 medium-volume example).
# execve narrowed to real logged-in users (auid>=1000) excluding the unset sentinel,
# which excludes daemon/system activity. f3 §3.5: narrowing by -F is MEDIUM volume.
# Comparison fields are single-quoted (f3 §1 gotcha: unquoted > is a shell redirect).
-a always,exit -S execve -F 'auid>=1000' -F 'auid!=unset' -k execve
